# Legacy WordPress URLs -> new site sections. 301s preserve inbound link
# equity from old backlinks and search results. Splats also catch any
# sub-paths (e.g. old blog post permalinks under /method-marketers-blog/).
/marketing-strategy/*              /work      301
/branding/*                        /work      301
/marketing-creative/*              /work      301
/marketing-implementation/*        /work      301
/how-we-work/*                     /work      301
/whow-we-are/*                     /about     301
/who-we-are/*                      /about     301
/method-marketers-blog/*           /writing   301
/connect-with-method-marketing/*   /connect   301

# Legacy WordPress blog posts lived under /blog/. The journey-mapping post
# maps to its topical successor; everything else goes to the writing index.
/blog/actionable-marketing-insights-come-from-customer-journey-mapping/*  /writing/cx-became-a-religion  301
/blog/*                            /writing   301

# Everything else unknown -> styled 404 page with a real 404 status.
# Netlify serves exact prerendered files first, so real routes never hit this.
/*    /404.html    404
